Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author: LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page: 20
Edition:
Quote: cotton plant: mountain daisy of the genus Celmisia. There must be fifty or sixty species, many of which have leaves which vary from a silvery to green upper side and are like cotton wool on the underside .. As they flourish after a fire they also answer to the name fireweed.
